<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> See <a href="http://ebusiness.mit.edu/erik/" class="external text" title="http://ebusiness.mit.edu/erik/" rel="nofollow">Brynjolfsson, Erik</a>, <a href="http://www.mgmt.purdue.edu/directory/bio.asp?username=yuhu" class="external text" title="http://www.mgmt.purdue.edu/directory/bio.asp?username=yuhu" rel="nofollow">Yu (Jeffrey) Hu</a>, and <a href="http://www.heinz.cmu.edu/~mds/" class="external text" title="http://www.heinz.cmu.edu/~mds/" rel="nofollow">Michael D. Smith</a>, <a href="http://ssrn.com/abstract=400940" class="external text" title="http://ssrn.com/abstract=400940" rel="nofollow">"Consumer Surplus in the Digital Economy: Estimating the Value of Increased Product Variety at Online Booksellers"</a>, Management Science, Vol. 49, No. 11, November 2003, and the April 2003 <a href="http://ssrn.com/abstract=400940" class="external text" title="http://ssrn.com/abstract=400940" rel="nofollow">working paper version</a> available via the Social Science Research Network.</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> See <a href="http://ebusiness.mit.edu/erik/" class="external text" title="http://ebusiness.mit.edu/erik/" rel="nofollow">Brynjolfsson, Erik</a>, <a href="http://www.mgmt.purdue.edu/directory/bio.asp?username=yuhu" class="external text" title="http://www.mgmt.purdue.edu/directory/bio.asp?username=yuhu" rel="nofollow">Yu (Jeffrey) Hu</a>, and <a href="http://web.mit.edu/simester/Public/" class="external text" title="http://web.mit.edu/simester/Public/" rel="nofollow">Duncan Simester</a>, 2006, <a href="http://ssrn.com/abstract=953587" class="external text" title="http://ssrn.com/abstract=953587" rel="nofollow">"Goodbye Pareto Principle, Hello Long Tail: The Effect of Search Costs on the Concentration of Product Sales"</a>, which is available via the Social Science Research Network.</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> See <a href="http://ebusiness.mit.edu/erik/" class="external text" title="http://ebusiness.mit.edu/erik/" rel="nofollow">Brynjolfsson, Erik</a>, <a href="http://www.mgmt.purdue.edu/directory/bio.asp?username=yuhu" class="external text" title="http://www.mgmt.purdue.edu/directory/bio.asp?username=yuhu" rel="nofollow">Yu (Jeffrey) Hu</a>, and <a href="http://www.heinz.cmu.edu/~mds/" class="external text" title="http://www.heinz.cmu.edu/~mds/" rel="nofollow">Michael D. Smith</a>, <a href="http://ssrn.com/abstract=918142" class="external text" title="http://ssrn.com/abstract=918142" rel="nofollow">"From Niches to Riches: Anatomy of the Long Tail"</a>, which is available via the Social Science Research Network.</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.benkler.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.benkler.org/" rel="nofollow">Benkler, The Wealth of Networks</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.evolhumbehav.2006.10.002" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.evolhumbehav.2006.10.002" rel="nofollow">"Regular rates of popular culture change reflect random copying"</a> by R.A. Bentley, C.P. Lipo, H.A. Herzog &amp; M.W. Hahn (2007) in <i>Evolution and Human Behavior</i> 28(3): 151-158.</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/connected/main.jhtml?xml=/connected/2004/06/16/ecfpop16.xml&amp;sSheet=/connected/2004/06/14/ixconn.html" class="external text" title="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/connected/main.jhtml?xml=/connected/2004/06/16/ecfpop16.xml&amp;sSheet=/connected/2004/06/14/ixconn.html" rel="nofollow">"Why are they so popular?", Roger Highfield, in <i>The Daily Telegraph</i>, June 16, 2004.</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://journals.royalsociety.org/content/1n1x17lp0c0q65uj" class="external text" title="http://journals.royalsociety.org/content/1n1x17lp0c0q65uj" rel="nofollow">"Random drift and culture change"</a> by R.A. Bentley, M.W. Hahn &amp; S.J. Shennan (2007) in <i>Proceedings of the Royal Society B</i> 271: 1443-50</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://arXiv.org/abs/0808.1655" class="external text" title="http://arXiv.org/abs/0808.1655" rel="nofollow">"Shelf space strategy in long tail markets"</a> by R.A. Bentley, P. Ormerod and M.E. Madsen, arXive</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://internetstockblog.com/article/1175" class="external text" title="http://internetstockblog.com/article/1175" rel="nofollow">"Competition and The Long Tail"</a> by David Jackson.</li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.gdrc.org/icm/" class="external text" title="http://www.gdrc.org/icm/" rel="nofollow">The Global Development Research Center, Microcredit and Microfinance</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.uncdf.org/english/microfinance/" class="external text" title="http://www.uncdf.org/english/microfinance/" rel="nofollow">United Nations Capital Development Fund</a></li>
